00:44:56.809 --> 00:45:00.809
a historical novel set during
the Indian Independence Movement.

00:45:00.809 --> 00:45:06.089
Then I have the "Conch Bearer Trilogy", which
has the Conch Bearer,

00:45:06.089 --> 00:45:10.069
that's book one, "The Mirror of Fire and Dreaming";
and then recently,

00:45:10.069 --> 00:45:15.400
"Shadowland, their magical adventures".
Well, when I started writing the "Conch Bearer",

00:45:15.400 --> 00:45:19.720
it was partly in
response to my boys saying, "Mom, you've got

00:45:19.720 --> 00:45:22.580
to write a book that we can
read and enjoy."

00:45:22.580 --> 00:45:25.730
So they were very excited when I was writing
"Conch Bearer".

00:45:25.730 --> 00:45:31.289
Oh, I could not write it fast enough for them.
They read it right off of my computer, and

00:45:31.289 --> 00:45:36.069
they were tough critics,
that would be like, "Mom, this is not exciting.

00:45:36.069 --> 00:45:41.190
Change this."
Or "Mom, kids don't think like this.

00:45:41.190 --> 00:45:45.440
You're making this kid think like you.
You got to change this."

00:45:45.440 --> 00:45:50.089
So they were very helpful as critics at that
point.

00:45:50.089 --> 00:45:54.210
And also I gave the two main characters in
the "Conch Bearer" their

00:45:54.210 --> 00:45:58.210
names, Anand and Abhay and they thought that
was so cool.

00:45:58.210 --> 00:46:01.500
They were like in middle school and elementary
school at that time and

00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:05.859
they were like this is so cool.
And I immediately became the favorite parent

00:46:05.859 --> 00:46:12.029
in the household.
But yes, the sequel is when they got to high

00:46:12.029 --> 00:46:16.099
school, it was not as cool
and they were like "Mom, can you not tell

00:46:16.099 --> 00:46:19.079
people that those characters
are named after us?"

00:46:19.079 --> 00:46:23.930
But now that one of them has gone to college,
well, it's kind of

00:46:23.930 --> 00:46:26.539
getting back to being cool again to be in
a book.

00:46:26.539 --> 00:46:30.759
So who knows?
This is a story in progress.

00:46:30.759 --> 00:46:35.990
But I think overall, they're kind of excited
by the fact that I do

00:46:35.990 --> 00:46:39.630
write.
Now the one who's in college is kind of excited

00:46:39.630 --> 00:46:43.019
because some of my
books are taught in college and his literature

00:46:43.019 --> 00:46:47.780
